  "detailedRequirements": "This is another challenge in the series for Cloud Hub, where we want to improve on our react web application. We have done a long series of challenges to build our Node API and now we are starting to put it to work. Our API currently has a limit for the number of users and applications that you can get with each call. We want to enable infinite scrolling to continue to call the API for more data, and we want to turn on sorting to call back to the API. Another <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/challenge-details/30053976/?type=develop\">challenge</a> is updating the API, but as long as the calls pass a param sort with the column names, we will worry about connecting the two after the challenge.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Requirements</strong><br />\n1. Implement a handler for the Griddle-React `externalChangeSort` property that calls the existing Redux action handler with the currently sorted column.<br />\n2. Make sure to implement helper functions to pass from the page components down to the ListPage child - keeping state managed in one place (the parent page component connected to the store). &nbsp;see <a href=\"https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/multiple-components.html\">React Documentation</a><br />\n3. Add sort parameter (sortColumn) to fetchApplications or fetchEmployees that specifies the column name and the direction of sort using this format: &quot;+columnName&quot; or &quot;-columnName&quot; or &ldquo;+columnOneName&rdquo;<br />\n4. Implement infinite scroll for Applications and Employees pages using Griddle-React<br />\n<br />\nES6 syntax is preferred, as Babel has been setup to handle transpiling the syntax to the current JavaScript standard.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Notes</strong><br />\n1. For an example of Inifinite Scroll using external data provided by a Flux implementation, see the Marty.js example referenced in this Github issue&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/GriddleGriddle/Griddle/issues/55\">https://github.com/GriddleGriddle/Griddle/issues/55</a><br />\n2. The video should focus on showing the API call functionality while using the employees page. The API source code in the forums will return 5 records for each call.&nbsp;",
